rops":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"I want this to be my zen garden, with a structure that inspires writing."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Luckily, Obsidian is the bomb digitty and built-in features and community plugins that allows us to fix this up."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h2","props":{"id":"cleaning-up-the-sidebar"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Cleaning up the sidebar"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"There's a handy community plugin called "},{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"https://github.com/Oliver-Akins/file-hider","rel":["nofollow"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"File Hider"}]},{"type":"text","value":" by Oliver Akins. When installed and enabled, you can right-click the folders and files you want to hide from the sidebar."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"img","props":{"alt":"hiding node_modules directory using file hider plugin","src":"https://cln.sh/mm4xqf8Q+"},"children":[]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Click "},{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{"className":[]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Hide Folder"}]},{"type":"text","value":" and "},{"type":"element","tag":"em","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"poof"}]},{"type":"text","value":" the folder is now hidden. You can hide as many files and folders as you want to make the space as clean as you want."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"If you ever want to re-show the folder, you have to go to the "},{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{"className":[]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"File Hider"}]},{"type":"text","value":" settings in the Community Plugins section and click the toggle to show the files again."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"NOTE:"}]},{"type":"text","value":" If you hide the folders and then disable and/or remove the File Hider plugin, the files and folders will continue to be hidden. To fix this, re-install and enable the plugin and ensure you re-show the hidden folders."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h3","props":{"id":"filter-relevant-search-results"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Filter relevant search results"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"You can \"exclude\" files and folders from search results."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Exclude is in quotes because Obsidian will still show these files in Quick Switcher and link suggestions. But, it looks like they are less likely to appear as a suggestion and only appear when explicitly searched for."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Here is my Excluded files list:"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"img","props":{"alt":"my excluded files","src":"https://cln.sh/Sth4lDRJ+"},"children":[]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"I hide the same directories and files that I hid using the File Hider plugin."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h2","props":{"id":"conclusion"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Conclusion"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Our Obsidian vaults are now cleaned up and less likely to distract us with unnecessary files and search results."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Slowly but surely we'll achieve the perfect digital zen garden."}]}],"toc":{"title":"","searchDepth":2,"depth":2,"links":[{"id":"problem","depth":2,"text":"Problem"},{"id":"cleaning-up-the-sidebar","depth":2,"text":"Cleaning up the sidebar","children":[{"id":"filter-relevant-search-results","depth":3,"text":"Filter relevant search results"}]},{"id":"conclusion","depth":2,"text":"Conclusion"}]}},"_type":"markdown","_id":"content:hidden-files-for-a-cleaner-obsidian.md","_source":"content","_file":"hidden-files-for-a-cleaner-obsidian.md","_stem":"hidden-files-for-a-cleaner-obsidian","_extension":"md"},{"_path":"/simple-obsidian-css-adjustments","_dir":"","_draft":false,"_partial":false,"_locale":"","title":"Simple Obsidian CSS Adjustments","description":"","date":"2024-11-10T22:06","topics":["obsidian","css"],"draft":false,"ignore":false,"created_at":"2024-11-10T22:06","last_modified":"2024-11-11T09:39","body":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"element","tag":"h2","props":{"id":"problem"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Problem"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"A recurring pain point for me in Obsidian is the default image behavior. I believe it simply renders the image to the image's default dimensions or the max Obsidian window dimensions, whichever is smaller."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Taking a screenshot on a Mac creates a relatively large image, so when I paste it into Obsidian, it takes up an uncomfortable amount of space, filling up the entire Obsidian editor, making it difficult to work in."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Ideally, the images I work with are re-sized and optimized for my blog and notes. But the reality is, I haven't found an effective solution that is as convenient as Imgur. I do a lot of my writing while on my phone, so having a mobile solution is essential."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h2","props":{"id":"inject-css-file"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Inject CSS File"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"This solution is simple. We'll be inspecting the element(s) we want to change using the built-in dev tools, and writing css that will override it."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Create a directory called "},{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{"className":[]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"snippets"}]},{"type":"text","value":" in your Obsidian vault's "},{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{"className":[]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":".obsidian"}]},{"type":"text","value":" directory."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Within snippets, create a css file. I called mine "},{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{"className":[]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"image_size.css"}]},{"type":"text","value":" but you can name it whatever you want."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"In your Obsidian settings, navigate to the Appearances tab and scroll to the "},{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{"className":[]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"CSS Snippets"}]},{"type":"text","value":" section. You should see it has loaded your newly created "},{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{"className":[]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"image_size.css"}]},{"type":"text","value":" file. Make sure to toggle it on."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Your css file should now be injected into your Obsidian view. Any changes you make to the css using this file will reflect in your Obsidian editor."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Here is my "},{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{"className":[]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"image_size.css"}]},{"type":"text","value":" file:"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"pre","props":{"code":"// image_size.css\nimg {\n    max-height: 600px;\n    border-radius: 20px;\n    box-shadow: rgba(100, 100, 111, 0.2) 0px 7px 29px 0px;\n}\n\n@media screen and (max-width: 768px) {\n    img {\n        max-height: 400px;\n    }\n}\n\n.markdown-source-view.mod-cm6 .cm-content > img {\n    margin: 0 auto !important;\n}\n"},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{"__ignoreMap":""},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"// image_size.css\nimg {\n    max-height: 600px;\n    border-radius: 20px;\n    box-shadow: rgba(100, 100, 111, 0.2) 0px 7px 29px 0px;\n}\n\n@media screen and (max-width: 768px) {\n    img {\n        max-height: 400px;\n    }\n}\n\n.markdown-source-view.mod-cm6 .cm-content > img {\n    margin: 0 auto !important;\n}\n"}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"This controls the image dimensions a bit and centers them. Here's an example:"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"img","props":{"alt":"ios device screenshot centered in obsidian editor","src":"https://cln.sh/N1XqL4Md+"},"children":[]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h2","props":{"id":"obsidian-devtools"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Obsidian Devtools"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"To view the html and css Obsidian uses, we need to open the devtools."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The keyboard shortcut to open the devtools are "},{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{"className":[]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"cmd + option + i "}]},{"type":"text","value":" on macOS and "},{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{"className":[]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"ctrl + shift + i"}]},{"type":"text","value":" on a windows machine."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Obsidian is a Chromium application, so the interface will look similar if you've worked in Chromium browsers before."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"You should be able to identify the element(s) you are interested in adjusting and now write the css needed to make the adjustments."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"img","props":{"alt":"devtools open in an obsidian editor","src":"https://cln.sh/PcWLJY4g+"},"children":[]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h2","props":{"id":"resources"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Resources"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"ul","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"https://help.obsidian.md/Extending+Obsidian/CSS+snippets","rel":["nofollow"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Obsidian CSS Snippets"}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"https://publish.obsidian.md/hub/04+-+Guides%2C+Workflows%2C+%26+Courses/Guides/How+to+Style+Obsidian","rel":["nofollow"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"How to Style Obsidian"}]}]}]}],"toc":{"title":"","searchDepth":2,"depth":2,"links":[{"id":"problem","depth":2,"text":"Problem"},{"id":"inject-css-file","depth":2,"text":"Inject CSS File"},{"id":"obsidian-devtools","depth":2,"text":"Obsidian Devtools"},{"id":"resources","depth":2,"text":"Resources"}]}},"_type":"markdown","_id":"content:simple-obsidian-css-adjustments.md","_source":"content","_file":"simple-obsidian-css-adjustments.md","_stem":"simple-obsidian-css-adjustments","_extension":"md"},{"_path":"/obsidian-git-on-ios","_dir":"","_draft":false,"_partial":false,"_locale":"","title":"Obsidian Git on iOS","description":"A step-by-step guide on how to connect your obsidian vault that is stored on Github to your iOS device.","date":"2024-11-08T00:00:00.000Z","topics":["mobile","iOS","obsidian","blogging"],"draft":false,"ignore":false,"created_at":"2024-11-09T10:02","last_modified":"2024-11-09T23:03","body":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"A step-by-step guide on how to connect your obsidian vault that is stored on Github to your iOS device."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","v